The '''Cheltenham Food & Drink Festival''' was founded in 2008 as an out-door festival held in [[Montpellier, Cheltenham|Montpellier Gardens]], [[Cheltenham]] to promote awareness of food, drinks, chefs, and restaurants. The focus is on Cheltenham and the county of [[Gloucestershire]] but has national exhibitors as well as local exhibitors. The Festival is held over three days each June and has around 19,000 visitors each year. [[The Hairy Bikers]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Hairy Bikers|title=Food and Drink|url=http://metro.co.uk/2008/06/17/food-and-drink-whats-cooking-in-the-west-country-199583/|accessdate=2 January 2013|newspaper=Metro|date=17 June 2008}}</ref> [[MasterChef (UK TV series)|Masterchef]] 2009 winner [[Mat Follas]], [[Antonio Carluccio]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Carluccio|first=Antonio|title=Glorious food!|url=http://www.thisisgloucestershire.co.uk/Glorious-food/story-11915723-detail/story.html|work=thisisgloucestershire|publisher=Northcliffe Media Limited|accessdate=2 January 2013}}</ref> and Celebrity Masterchef 2011 winner [[Phil Vickery (rugby union)|Phil Vickery]] have all cooked at the Festival.
